-- Brazilian Stock Movers: Brasil Insurance, Camargo, Qualicorp
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-03-19T20:48:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-19/brazilian-stock-movers-brasil-insurance-camargo-qualicorp.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  index advanced 0.1 percent to 67,730.31.  Brasil Insurance Participacoes e Administracao SA  (BRIN3
BS) gained 2.3 percent to 20.15 reais, the highest since March
1. Banco BTG Pactual SA said the company is its top pick in the
 insurance industry  and recommended clients buy the stock,
according to a research note dated today.  Camargo Correa Desenvolvimento Imobiliario SA (CCIM3)  (CCIM3 BS)
jumped 8.5 percent to 4.60 reais, the highest since July 29. The
homebuilder’s parent, Camargo Correa SA, plans to buy its
outstanding shares and delist the company’s stock, according to
a regulatory filing.  Qualicorp SA (QUAL3)  (QUAL3 BS) rose 0.1 percent to 15.91 reais,
after earlier gaining as much as 1.5 percent. The health
insurance broker said its unit Qualicorp Corretora de Seguros SA
agreed to buy Fidelitas Corretora de Seguros SA’s client
portfolio, according to a March 16 regulatory filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
